subject: ComfyUI_String_Function_Tree
question: What is ComfyUI_String_Function_Tree?
answer: ComfyUI_String_Function_Tree is a custom node for ComfyUI that was modded from the original String Function in ComfyUI-Custom-Scripts to allow plugging more stuff into the original function.

subject: ComfyUI_String_Function_Tree
question: What are the steps to install the original ComfyUI-Custom-Scripts?
answer: To install the original ComfyUI-Custom-Scripts, open a terminal or command line interface, navigate to the `ComfyUI/custom_nodes/` directory, and run the command `git clone https://github.com/pythongosssss/ComfyUI-Custom-Scripts.git`.

subject: ComfyUI_String_Function_Tree
question: What is the command to install the customized version?
answer: To install the customized version of ComfyUI_String_Function_Tree, run the command `git clone https://github.com/wolfden/ComfyUi_String_Function_Tree.git`.

subject: ComfyUI_String_Function_Tree
question: How do I access the new node in ComfyUI after installation?
answer: After restarting ComfyUI, you will find a new menu under the utils submenu called String Function Tree. Clicking on it will add a new node to your workflow.
